News24 Correspondent Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - Sars custom officials had to sift through cargo boxes of dried fish &ndash; to find the real stink &ndash; when they seized crystal meth with a street value of R30m at OR Tambo Airport over the weekend. &ldquo;Sars customs officials and detector dogs intercepted 100kg of Crystal Meth,&rdquo; Sars said in a statement about the drug bust which took place on Friday. At the transit shed, the 33 cans of &lsquo;Devon King&rsquo;s vegetable oil' &ndash; weighing 100 kilograms &ndash; which had been packed in cardboard boxes also containing loose pieces of dried fish, were tested. &nbsp;They were found to contain crystal meth. &ldquo;The shipment originated in Cameroon via Istanbul on a flight from Turkey to Johannesburg.&rdquo;The goods have been handed over to police for further investigation. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.